Feature: Admin Permissions    Background:     Given the following users exist:       | email             | admin |         | admin@example.com | true  |       | user@example.com  | false |     And the following posts exist:         | title   | body             | user_email        |       | Post 1  | Body for post 1  | user@example.com  |       | Post 2  | Body for post 2  | user@example.com  |    Scenario: Admin can see all posts     Given I am logged in as an admin     When I visit the posts page       Then I should see 'Post 1'      And I should see 'Post 2'    Scenario: Admin can manage other user's post     Given I am logged in as an admin       When I visit the page for 'Post 1'     Then I should see an 'Edit' link     And I should see a 'Delete' link      Scenario: Non-admin cannot manage other user's post     Given I am logged in as a non-admin     When I visit the page for 'Post 1'       Then I should not see an 'Edit' link     And I should not see a 'Delete' link